---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Hargrove Wealth Advisory collects, uses, protects, and never sells your personal information."
  noindex={false}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container fade-up">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy.</h1>
      <hr class="gold-rule" />
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: January 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow legal">
      <p class="legal__intro fade-up">
        Hargrove Wealth Advisory ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to
        protecting it. As a registered investment adviser, we are also bound by federal and state
        privacy regulations that apply specifically to financial services firms. This policy
        describes what information we collect, how we use it, and the controls you have over it.
      </p>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect information you provide to us directly — when you fill out our contact form,
          schedule a consultation, become a client, or correspond with us by phone or email. This
          may include your name, address, phone number, email address, date of birth, Social
          Security number, employment information, financial account information, investment
          objectives, and other details necessary to provide our services.
        </p>
        <p>
          We also collect limited information automatically when you visit our website, including
          basic analytics data such as the pages you visited, your approximate location based on
          IP address, the device and browser you used, and the date and time of your visit. We do
          not use this information to identify you personally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use the information you provide to deliver our advisory services: building your
          financial plan, managing your investment accounts, preparing reports, responding to your
          questions, meeting regulatory and tax-reporting obligations, and communicating with you
          about your account and our firm. We do not use your information for any purpose
          unrelated to providing you with financial advisory services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> Ever. We do not rent it, trade
          it, or share it with marketers. Period.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do share information with a limited set of service providers who are necessary to
          deliver our services — such as the custodian that holds your accounts (e.g. Schwab or
          Fidelity), our portfolio reporting and financial planning software providers, our CPA
          partners (only with your authorization), and our internal accounting and compliance
          systems. Every third party we use is bound by confidentiality requirements and is
          permitted to use your information only for the purpose of supporting our services.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may also disclose information when required by law — for example, in response to a
          valid subpoena, court order, or regulatory examination — and we will notify you of such
          a disclosure where we are legally permitted to do so.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          We maintain administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect your
          information. These include encrypted storage of sensitive data, role-based access
          controls, multi-factor authentication for all employees, secure document portals for
          exchanging financial information (we strongly discourage clients from sending account
          numbers or tax documents over standard email), and annual security training for all
          staff. No system is perfectly secure, but we treat your information with the seriousness
          a financial firm should.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>request a copy of the personal information we hold about you;</li>
          <li>request that we correct any inaccuracies in that information;</li>
          <li>request that we delete information we are not legally required to retain;</li>
          <li>opt out of any non-essential communications (we do not engage in marketing email of any kind, but you may also unsubscribe from any communications you receive);</li>
          <li>file a complaint with your state's regulator or the SEC if you believe we have mishandled your information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at the email address below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Cookies and Website Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses minimal first-party cookies necessary for the site to function. We use
          a privacy-respecting analytics tool that does not track you across other sites and does
          not require a cookie banner under most regulations. You can block all cookies in your
          browser settings without losing functionality on our site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are not directed to children under 18, and we do not knowingly collect
          information from anyone under 18.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or
          regulatory requirements. When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top
          of this page and, for material changes, notify active clients directly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="fade-up">
        <h2>Contact for Privacy Matters</h2>
        <p>
          If you have a question, concern, or request related to your privacy, please reach out:
        </p>
        <p class="legal__contact">
          <strong>Hargrove Wealth Advisory</strong><br />
          Attn: Chief Compliance Officer<br />
          1240 Financial District Blvd, Suite 800<br />
          New York, NY 10005<br />
          <a href="mailto:privacy@hargrovewealth.com">privacy@hargrovewealth.com</a><br />
          <a href="tel:+15552804400">(555) 280-4400</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-block: var(--space-9) var(--space-7);
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 40% 60% at 90% 0%, rgba(201, 168, 76, 0.07), transparent 70%),
      var(--color-bg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-meta {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal {
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal__intro {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal section + section {
    margin-top: var(--space-7);
  }

  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal strong {
    color: var(--color-gold-light);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(201, 168, 76, 0.4);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color var(--t-base) var(--ease);
  }

  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-light);
  }

  .legal__contact {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
    line-height: 2;
  }
</style>
